  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582497616-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582497616-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582497616-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582497616-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582497616-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616582505881-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616582505881-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616582505881-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616582505881-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1616582505881-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>spelt </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>and cook, covered, for 25-30 min, stirring occasionally, until the spelt is tender with a slight bite</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1616582527208-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1616582527208-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1616582527208-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1616582527208-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1616582527208-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the spelt is cooking, chop the <strong>basil </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582543791-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582543791-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582543791-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582543791-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582543791-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add most of the<strong> chopped basil</strong> (save some for garnish!) to a <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bash to a paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and the juice of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1] </span><strong>lemon </strong>and give it a good mix up – this is your<strong> basil drizzle</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4]</span> wedges</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1616582574634-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1616582574634-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1616582574634-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1616582574634-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1616582574634-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the spelt is cooking, trim the woody ends off the <strong>asparagus</strong>, then chop in half and set the <strong>asparagus</strong> <strong>tips</strong> aside and roughly chop the <strong>asparagus</strong> <strong>stalks</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> asparagus tips</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray and sprinkle over <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 6-7 min or until the<strong> </strong>asparagus tips are cooked and the cheese is melted and crisp – these are your <strong>cheesy asparagus tips</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1616582603738-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1616582603738-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1616582603738-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1616582603738-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1616582603738-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the spelt is almost cooked, add the <strong>blanched peas</strong> and<strong> chopped asparagus stalks</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until tender</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>lighter</strong> <strong>asparagus & pea speltotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582645615-x200.jpg",
